     <body>
     <div type="encomium">
   <head>To the Authour.</head>
   <l>IF grauer headdes shall count it ouerlight,</l>
   <l>To treate of <hi>Loue:</hi> say thou to them: <hi>A staine</hi>
   </l>
   <l>Is incident vnto the finest die.</l>
   <l>And yet no staine at all it is for thee,</l>
   <l>These layes of <hi>Loue,</hi> as myrth to melancholy,</l>
   <l>To fellowe fast thy sad <hi>Antigone,</hi>
   </l>
   <l>Which may beare out a broader worke then this,</l>
   <l>Compyl'd with iudgement, order, and with arte.</l>
   <l>And shrowde thee vnder shadowe of his winges,</l>
   <l>Whose gentle heart, and head with learning fraight</l>
   <l>Shall yeld thee gracious fauour and defence.</l>
   <closer>
      <signed>G. Peele.</signed>
   </closer>
</div>
